{
  "stem": "15197.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I remember also before I left Poland, and before I worked in the Jewish committee, that the pogrom in Kielce took place, a Polish city where it was a Jewish community from a small group of survivors.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was pogrom by-- it was by Poles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the Polish police, and even at that time, the Russian police did not take care, did not control the situation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And over 40 people were killed at that time, saying that the Jews are taking because of some rumor, the Jews were taking blood from a Polish boy to prepare the matzahs for Pesach for the holiday, for Eastern holiday, which was a rumor later that they killed the boy.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The boy was alive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They found the boy, but nevertheless, after the boy said the truth, for the people already were killed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a Polish government, but it was under the Soviet-- not occupation, but supervision.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Later on, after the people were killed, they controlled the situation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, not long ago, they told me that in July, it's going to be a monument put up for the-- over for the killed Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was a Pogrom, and this was after the German-- there were not anymore German pogrom by the Poles.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was anti-Semitism in the towns, on trains, and people were afraid to go back to the places and smaller towns.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But even a city like Kielce, it was a polgrom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, I didn't see the ghetto anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I just saw rubble.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my first instinct when I came back was to go to the cemetery, and to put up at tomb for my father.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
